                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13020652" author="stack" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 19:40:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good idea.  What would we do?  A state on the zk ensemble?  Don&apos;t we have a zk dump already?  zk.jsp?  This shows a bunch of stats including who&apos;s connected.  Does that work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020676" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 22:04:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Copied code from ZKUtil.dump()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13022311" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2011 19:10:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can I not see the number of connections by looking at the zk.jsp page?  If so, does this change add anything?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13022319" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2011 19:22:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The intent was to expose connection count on master.jsp so that we don&apos;t need to visit zk.jsp&lt;br/&gt;
IP addresses are listed under Quorum Server Statistics on zk.jsp which aren&apos;t easy to interpret, especially if there&apos;re hundreds of clients. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13455359" author="lhofhansl" created="Thu, 13 Sep 2012 22:10:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about this one, Ted?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13455366" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 13 Sep 2012 22:20:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this one would be good to have.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15671644" author="esteban" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2016 21:10:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;zk.jsp (ZKUtil.dump() see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2692&quot; title=&quot;Master rewrite and cleanup for 0.90&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2692&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2692&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) from the Master UI already provides the total number of connections to ZK open.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
